@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<div class="mx-auto max-w-[85rem] px-4 py-10 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 lg:py-14">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl">
        <div class="text-center">
            <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-800 sm:text-4xl mb-5">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-6 text-gray-700">
            <p>Thank you for visiting our application. We value your privacy and want to make sure you understand how your information is used and protected. This Privacy Policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, and your rights regarding your data.</p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800">1. Information We Collect</h2>
            <p>We may collect personal information such as your name, email address, phone number, and other details when you interact with our application. This information may be collected directly from you when you fill out forms or indirectly through automated means such as cookies.</p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800">2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
            <p>The information we collect is used to provide, maintain, and improve our services. We may also use your information to communicate with you regarding updates, changes to policies, or other necessary notifications related to our application.</p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800">3. Data Sharing</h2>
            <p>We do not share your personal information with third parties unless required by law or in the event that it is necessary for the operation of the application, such as service providers who help maintain the application.</p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800">4. Data Security</h2>
            <p>We take data security seriously and use reasonable measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. However, no method of transmission over the internet is entirely secure, and we cannot guarantee the absolute security of your data.</p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800">5. Your Rights</h2>
            <p>You have the right to access, correct, or delete your personal information. If you have any questions about your data or this policy, please contact us through the appropriate channels provided on our website.</p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800">6. Changes to This Policy</h2>
            <p>We reserve the right to update this Privacy Policy at any time. Changes will be effective immediately upon posting, and we encourage you to review this policy periodically.</p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800">7. Contact Us</h2>
            <p>If you have questions or concerns about this policy, please create a GitHub issue.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
